summary:
Hello, thank you for visiting my profile! üòÑ
My name is Natalia, and I would like to tell you a little more about myself. üë©üèª‚Äçüíº

I have a degree in Advertising and Public Relations, which I obtained quite a few years ago, when internal communication was still mostly one-way, and focused purely on informational needs üòÖ. At that time to create a strategy, you would just focus with one eye üëÅÔ∏è on the external client's needs, and with the other üëÅÔ∏è on the product the company wanted to sell.

With enthusiasm to learn new ways of doing things, I went to Germany. There, I found new challenges and areas of learning that combined communication, marketing, and technology in an international environment. From there I went to the Netherlands, where I experienced new challenges and opportunities, and had the chance to change sectors, functions, and competencies.

Years later, it was time to evaluate purpose, values, social challenges, motivation and areas of development. ‚û°Ô∏è Reskilling process:

. Official Master's in HR-Organization and Talent Management
. Master in Workplace Wellbeing
. Expert in Coaching with NLP
...

In my "I believe" section:

- The world is changing too fast. I believe that in order to maintain a stable business, it is essential to be able to adapt quickly, and take care of üëÄ, support üëÄ, and develop üëÄour internal customers.  
- I believe we all know the theory, and it's important to put it into real practice. üöÄ
- I believe that the willingness to improve, belong, and contribute are essential elements of the human condition. üôåüèº

->I collaborate with Global Leadership ü§ù

Currently, I am looking for a professional project where I can add value, grow professionally and personally,, and contribute to sustainable and effective human talent development. üí™üèº

Thank you for your time and attention! üíñ
Now you know a little more about me. I invite you to connect through LinkedIn and keep the conversation going. üòä
